values:
Once a month, for a week, I will be taking an almost absolute hiatus from the internet (I will check my e-mail once a day for e-mails from family/professors/classmates about class; research on the internet is obviously not going to be cut out if I need it for class).

I'm taking a break because I realized that I've been wasting a lot of time on the internet, and I plan on using that week to get caught up on stuff and to just enjoy everything my life has to offer. I can survive without the internet. I plan on also using that time to draw closer to God.

If you need me between the dates, call me or talk to me face to face. If you ABSOLUTELY have to e-mail me, make it apparent in the subject line that it is a matter of extreme importance. 

I realized that if I do this once a month, that's 12 weeks. 12 weeks is about 3 months. 3 months is 25% of the year.&nbsp; That's a ton of time I can invest in a better way.&nbsp; That's 3 more months of time I can devote to serving God.

Do I have exact dates planned out?&nbsp; Not right now.&nbsp; But I may at some point, set dates to be internet-less every month.

This time around, it will be from February 18-24. &nbsp;

Going along with this, I also try to avoid the internet on Sundays, so I can give the whole day to God. &nbsp;

For those on Flickr, I will still be taking pictures for Project 365, just I'll be late in posting them. &nbsp;

Here's to becoming a better person!!!

